{
  "name": "mac-news-business-is-apple-prepared-for-727ea9",
  "title": "Is Apple Prepared for a Succession?",
  "description": "MacNewsWorld analysis of Apple's succession planning after Steve Jobs's pancreatic cancer disclosure and 30-day medical leave (August 2004). Peter Kastner, executive vice president at Aberdeen Group, plays down near-term governance risk \u2014 the head of sales is running the company during back-to-school season \u2014 but the article broadly raises concern about Apple's lack of disclosed succession plan.",
